## Test Case 2: Email Verification (Negative Case)

### Objective
Verify that a user cannot log in without confirming email registration.

### Preconditions
- Application loads successfully (200 OK)

### Test Data
- Email: non-existing or unconfirmed email
- Password: valid password

### Steps
1. Open the application
2. Click on the "Register" button
3. Fill in all required fields with valid data
4. Complete registration without confirming email
5. Attempt to log in using the registered credentials

### Expected Result
- Login attempt fails
- User is not able to access the system without email confirmation

---

## Test Case 3: Registration with Invalid Password (Too Short)

### Objective
Verify that registration fails when the password does not meet minimum length requirements.

### Preconditions
- Application loads successfully (200 OK)

### Test Data
- Password: less than 8 characters (e.g. !1Aaaaa)
- Other fields: valid data

### Steps
1. Open the application
2. Click on the "Register" button
3. Fill in all required fields with valid data except password
4. Enter a password shorter than 8 characters
5. Click on the "Register" button

### Expected Result
- Registration fails
- Error message is displayed indicating password requirements
